The paper discusses a machine learning approach (federated learning) and uses optimization theory to reformulate the problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of protection functions and regularization factors suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the distributed nature of federated learning suggests that the paper may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
